# Force LF endings on every text file across all checkouts.
#
# The hook's pin chain (lib/lead-pretool-hook.py:_PIN_FILES + the
# trust anchor on lib/install-hook.ps1) is byte-exact: every pin
# entry stores SHA256 of the on-disk file, so a single CRLF byte
# changes the hash and trips _GENERIC_INTEGRITY = "denied:
# integrity check failed".
#
# GitHub Actions windows-latest runners default to
# core.autocrlf=true, which silently rewrites LF -> CRLF on
# checkout. That made the CI hook-fixture matrix fail closed
# (run 25471550505) while local checkouts (core.autocrlf=false)
# passed. Pinning eol=lf via .gitattributes overrides
# autocrlf for this repo on every platform.
#
# Repo is pure-text -- no binary assets to exempt.
* text=auto eol=lf
